        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Required for polymorphic O-glycosylation of the serine-rich repeat protein in this bacteria. A stabilizing protein that is part of the accessory SecA2/SecY2 system specifically required to export serine-rich repeat cell wall proteins usually encoded upstream in the same operon. The GtfA-GtfB complex adds GlcNAc from UDP-GlcNAc to the substrate protein, attaching the first sugar residue. Stabilizes the glycosylation activity of GtfA. Has no N-acetylglucosaminyl transferase activity on its own"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
